the active participle of the verb أَذْهَبَ (ʔaḏhaba, “to gild”), denominal verb from ذَهَب (ḏahab, “gold”).\n\nDerived from the passive participle of the verb أَذْهَبَ (ʔaḏhaba, “to gild”), denominal verb from ذَهَب (ḏahab, “gold”).\n\nDenominal verb from مَذْهَب (maḏhab, “sect”)."},"ipa":["/mað.hab/","/mu.ðah.hib/","/mu.ðah.hab/","/muð.hib/","/muð.hab/","/mað.ha.ba/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n14123","headword_ar":"مَذْهَبٌ","root":"*hb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is an inf. n.: (JK, A, K:) ―         -b2-  and also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaAb","text_ar":"ذَهَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"going,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a time thereof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK.) ―         -b3-  [Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place to which one goes:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHoDarN","text_ar":"مَحْضَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b4-  And hence,] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place to which one goes for the purpose of satisfying a want of nature; a privy;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutawaD~aA^N","text_ar":"مُتَوَضَّاٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (JK, A, K, TA;) in the dial. of the people of El-Hijáz. (JK, A, TA.) ―         -b5-  [Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A way by which one goes"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goes away."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b6-  And hence, as in several exs. in the first paragraph of this art.,] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A way, course, mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of acting"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conduct"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K, TA:) (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a way that one pursues in respect of doctrines and practices"},{"kind":"text","text":"in religion &c.; and particularly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a way of believing, opining, thinking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"judging;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a belief, a creed, a persuasion, a doctrine, an opinion, a tenet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a body of tenets"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"articles of belief;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an opinion"},{"kind":"text","text":"in, or respecting, religion; and, accord. to Es-Sarakustee,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an innovation"},{"kind":"text","text":"in religion: (Msb:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahobN","text_ar":"ذَهْبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same. (JK, TA.) [The pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*aAhibu","text_ar":"مَذَاهِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*awuw ma*aAhibu","text_ar":"ذَوُو مَذَاهِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Persuasions,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"persons holding particular tenets in religion"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b7-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Origin:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ks, Lh, K:) so in the sayings,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA yudoraY lahu A^ayona ma*ohabahu","text_ar":"مَا يُدْرَى لَهُ اَيْنَ مَذْهَبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA yudoraY lahu","text_ar":"لَا يُدْرَى لَهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*ohabN","text_ar":"مَذْهَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It is not known whence is his origin."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ks, Lh, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["JK","A","K","Msb","TA","Ks","Lh"]},{"entry_id":"n14124","headword_ar":"مُذْهَبٌ","root":"*hb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Gilt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"done over with gold;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu*ah~abN","text_ar":"مُذَهَّبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahiybN","text_ar":"ذَهِيبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, K.) ―         -b2-  Also sing. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*aAhibu","text_ar":"مَذَاهِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Skins gilt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, JK, TA,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having gilt tines,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stripes, regularly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uniformly, succeeding one another:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gilt straps"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thongs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"variegated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"figured,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garments of the kind called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwd","text_ar":"بُرُود"},{"kind":"text","text":": (JK, TA:) [or it is applied as an epithet to such garments; for] you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burodN mu*ohabN","text_ar":"بُرْدٌ مُذْهَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) The pl. above mentioned is also applied [as an epithet] to swords [app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Adorned with gilding"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b3-  Applied to a horse,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Of a red colour tinged over with yellow;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kumayotN mu*ohabN","text_ar":"كُمَيْتٌ مُذْهَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a gilded bay colour"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, TA:) fem. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": the mare thus termed is of a clearer colour and thinner skin. (TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almu*ohabu","text_ar":"المُذْهَبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also a name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Kaabeh."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.)       -A3-  See also the next paragraph, in three places."}],"source_refs":["A","K","ISk","JK","TA","S"]},{"entry_id":"n14125","headword_ar":"مُذْهِبٌ","root":"*hb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A gilder."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b2-  ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almu*ohabu","text_ar":"المُذْهَبُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", explained by Lth as the name of (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain devil, said to be of the offspring of Iblees, who tempts reciters of the Kur-án in the performance of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the ablution termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlwuDuwo'","text_ar":"الوُضُوْء"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, * TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and on other occasions,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) is [said to be] correctly ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almu*ohibu","text_ar":"المُذْهِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] with kesr to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the devil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$yT","text_ar":"شيط"},{"kind":"text","text":",) as meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he who embellishes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"renders goodly in appearance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"acts of disobedience [to God], as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almuha*~ibu","text_ar":"المُهَذِّبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Fr, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h*b","text_ar":"هذب"},{"kind":"text","text":",) IDrd thinks that it is not [genuine] Arabic. (TA.) And accord. to the S and El-Kurtubee and many others, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihi mu*ohabN","text_ar":"بِهِ مُذْهَبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In him is"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a vain suggestion"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the devil"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"respecting the water, and"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"respecting"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the using much thereof in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wuDuwo'","text_ar":"وُضُوْء"},{"kind":"text","text":": [i. e. a vain suggestion that may induce him to think that the water is unfit, or deficient in quantity, or the like:] but accord. to the K, it is correctly"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almu*ohibu","text_ar":"المُذْهِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) Az says that the people of Baghdád apply the appellation"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu*ohibN","text_ar":"مُذْهِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"to (assumed tropical:)  A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who inspires vain suggestions;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and that the vulgar among them pronounce it ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu*ohabN","text_ar":"مُذْهَبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","K"]},{"entry_id":"n14127","headword_ar":"مُذَهَّبٌ","root":"*hb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu*ohabN","text_ar":"مُذْهَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}